  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "The phrase **\"subject to availability\"** means that something (e.g., a product, service, or opportunity) is only available if there is enough supply, capacity, or resources at the time of request. In other words, it is not guaranteed and depends on whether the item or service is still in stock, accessible, or available when you inquire or act.\n\n### Examples of usage:\n- **Hotels or flights:** \"Rates are subject to availability.\" (The price is valid if rooms or seats are still available when you book.)\n- **Products:** \"Free gift subject to availability.\" (You\u2019ll receive the gift only if there are enough in stock.)\n- **Events:** \"Tickets are subject to availability.\" (You can get a ticket only if they haven\u2019t sold out.)\n\nIn essence, it\u2019s a disclaimer to manage expectations and inform you that your request may not be fulfilled if the item or service is no longer available.",
